==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hyperoartia
<hw>Hy`per*o*ar"ti*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of marsipobranchs
including the lampreys. The suckerlike moth contains numerous teeth; the
nasal opening is in the middle of the head above, but it does not
connect with the mouth. See <er>Cyclostoma</er>, and
<er>Lamprey</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hyperodontidae</ent>⟦br⟧
